{
  "text": "We compared the results from our simulations with a few real-world examples. Figure 16 , left, shows video footage of a real lake shore reflecting and diffracting wind waves. The many small ripples are caused by non-linear phenomena but we are able to create a similar Fig. 10 . A 1-meter plane wave interacting with a cylinder. Our method (left), wavefront tracking [CITATION_1] (middle left), wave packets [CITATION_2] , water surface wavelets [CITATION_3] ] Fig. 11 . Comparison between the Water surface wavelets [CITATION_4] (top) and our method (bottom) in a more complex case. Spectrum of frequencies ranging from 0.05 to 10m. Table 2 . Timing information for the scene in Figure 15 for different resolutions of frequencies and grid. The linear system is not solved each frame (dt = 0.025) but each time step \u03b4 t . n s_total represents the total number of sources including all the frequencies.",
